        <para id="id213116">which can be seen from values in <link target-id="uid48"/>.</para>
        <para id="id213126">Johnson <link target-id="bid22"/> noted from Beylkin <link target-id="bid33"/> and Unser
<link target-id="bid24"/> that by using the moments of the autocorrelation function
of the scaling function, a relationship of the continuous scaling function
moments can be derived in the form</para><equation id="uid91">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mrow>
              <m:munderover>
